.TH "LDSYNC" "1" "Apr 14, 2026" "0.12" "mpiFileUtils"
.SH NAME
ldsync \- synchronize directory trees with bounded source symlink dereference
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ldsync [OPTION]... SRC DEST
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ldsync
is a thin wrapper around
.BR dsync (1)
that resolves the source path through symbolic links at most
.I N
hops before invoking
.BR dsync .
All other options and arguments are passed through unchanged.
.PP
This can be useful when the source argument itself is a symlink chain and one
wants deterministic one-hop (or N-hop) dereference behavior.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "-N, --source-link-depth " N
Follow the source path symlink chain for at most
.I N
hops before calling
.BR dsync .
.I N
must be a non-negative integer. The default value is
.BR 1 .
.TP
.B -h, --help
Print usage and exit.
.PP
Any option not listed above is passed directly to
.BR dsync .
.PP
ldsync parses wrapper options only before
.B -- .
Use
.B --
to pass remaining arguments directly to
.BR dsync .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Use default one-hop source symlink follow:
.B ldsync /src-link /backup
.TP
Follow source symlink chain up to 3 hops:
.B ldsync --source-link-depth 3 /src-link /backup
.TP
Disable source symlink dereference:
.B ldsync -N 0 /src-link /backup
.TP
Show dsync help through ldsync:
.B ldsync -- --help
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dsync (1),
.BR mpifileutils (1)
